<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,153,1259]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1088,1115]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Comments.</emphasis>
Compared with the other species that have a complete posterior transverse carina, short notauli, and closed areolet, head slightly transverse, light brown apical bands on tergites 1–3 and frontal orbits entirely yellow up to occiput, unlike in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[464,584,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaris">
<emphasis box="[464,584,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. malaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[637,803,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlaxcalensis">
<emphasis box="[637,803,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. tlaxcalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; mesoscutum reddish-brown, unlike in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[1246,1389,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[1246,1389,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,285,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khalaimi">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. khalaimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; flagellum shorter and stouter, basal flagellomere 1.4 × as long as wide, notaular lines not developed and spiracles of second tergite protruding, unlike in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2019" box="[735,897,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Orthocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montezuma">
<emphasis box="[735,897,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. montezuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
